SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-3-103(d), is amended by adding
the following as a new subdivision:
By July 1, 2025, and by each July 1 thereafter, explain how a public charter
school may dispute an alleged error in an allocation to its authorizer and explain the
procedures the authorizer must take.
SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 49-3-105, is amended by deleting
subsection (d) and substituting instead the following:
(d)
(1) The funding that a student generates pursuant to this section must be
administered and allocated by the department to the LEA in which the student is
a member for the duration of the student's membership in the LEA, except that:
(A) The funding a student generates pursuant to subdivision
(c)(3) must not be allocated to the LEA, but must be maintained by the
department; and
(B) The state share of the funding a public charter school student
generates for an LEA pursuant to this section must be allocated to the
LEA, but must be disbursed directly to the public charter school by the
department unless the public charter school is authorized by the
commission, as defined in ยง 49-13-104, or by the achievement school
district, as defined in ยง 49-1-614, in which case such funds must be
